<span id="freeTextContainer7602978140273193310"><b>3.45 stars rounded to 3</b><br/><br/><br/>This was my third Sidney Sheldon novel. It&apos;s a story about a woman facing Multiple Personality Disorder (MPD). The story is engaging, the narration is also fine, but the suspense and the plot twist could have been better. Having said that, the MPD thing makes it an absorbing read.<br/><br/>For fellow Indians out there, remember the movie, &quot;Bhool Bhulaiyaa&quot; starring Akshay Kumar and Vidya Balan in lead roles - the movie also deals with MPD and boy - it did that so well! The movie and</span>
  <span id="freeText7602978140273193310" style="display:none"><b>3.45 stars rounded to 3</b><br /><br /><br />This was my third Sidney Sheldon novel. It's a story about a woman facing Multiple Personality Disorder (MPD). The story is engaging, the narration is also fine, but the suspense and the plot twist could have been better. Having said that, the MPD thing makes it an absorbing read.<br /><br />For fellow Indians out there, remember the movie, "Bhool Bhulaiyaa" starring Akshay Kumar and Vidya Balan in lead roles - the movie also deals with MPD and boy - it did that so well! The movie and this book are quite analogous.</span>
