<div id="review_1774101121" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1774101121" />
    <a title="Ana Jupek" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/55423656-ana-jupek"><img alt="Ana Jupek" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1596237939p2/55423656.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1774101121?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ana Jupek" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ana Jupek" href="/user/show/55423656-ana-jupek">Ana Jupek</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9789536232697" href="/book/show/13159292-ispri-aj-mi-svoje-snove">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1774101121" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer640344222245132492">Well,to be honest i gave it a 3 * just because it is S.Sheldon. And i loved him....when i was around 15... I felt nostalgic when my colleague gave me some old books her mother owned. Six of them are from S.Sheldon. I read 3 of his book (not that many i admit )but i was surprised abouth his writing style. . . Very easy going... like a screenplay in a way. I guess i should read Bloodline again. I was 14 when i tought that was a perfect book. . . I will read all of the books i got of course. .I jus</span>
  <span id="freeText640344222245132492" style="display:none">Well,to be honest i gave it a 3 * just because it is S.Sheldon. And i loved him....when i was around 15... I felt nostalgic when my colleague gave me some old books her mother owned. Six of them are from S.Sheldon. I read 3 of his book (not that many i admit )but i was surprised abouth his writing style. . . Very easy going... like a screenplay in a way. I guess i should read Bloodline again. I was 14 when i tought that was a perfect book. . . I will read all of the books i got of course. .I just tought his writing skills were more...adult... This kind of books are very easy to read. I hope i am not going to insult his fans by saying that this is *I will read on the beach style of book*(which i did) . <br />*spoiler alert <br />I assumed she had personality disorder way before it was revealed. . There was no surprise element which i believe author wanted to achieve . <br />It was very easy to see during a trial that she is just not going to be executed so trial felt pointless... <br />And it was not difficult to see that ending happening...<br />All in all.. i do recommend. Maybe it is just me. Maybe i expected too much. <br />*sorry for my spelling. English is not my first language</span>
  <a data-text-id="640344222245132492" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


