<div id="review_2357639398" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2357639398" />
    <a title="Jarvis " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15947944-jarvis"><img alt="Jarvis " src="https://s.gr-assets.com/images/nophoto/user/c_111x148.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2357639398?book_show_action=true">Apr 11, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jarvis " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jarvis " href="/user/show/15947944-jarvis">Jarvis </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8553505-tell-me-your-dreams">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Jarvis  by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/37827766-aditya-jain">Aditya Jain</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15947944-jarvis?shelf=ebook-audiobooks">ebook-audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15947944-jarvis?shelf=my-reviews">my-reviews</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15947944-jarvis?shelf=get-recommendations-by">get-recommendations-by</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2357639398" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer726971534003418209">4.5 stars rounded down to 4!<br/><br/>You know when you are listening a really loud rock song and you become oblivious to the world around you and become a part of an imaginary music video which is only in your head. And then the song finishes and you look at people around you sitting in silence completely unaware of the great music that was jamming in your headphones seconds ago. That is exactly how this book felt. There was so much going on in the book; I would read a bit, completely engrossed, and look</span>
  <span id="freeText726971534003418209" style="display:none">4.5 stars rounded down to 4!<br /><br />You know when you are listening a really loud rock song and you become oblivious to the world around you and become a part of an imaginary music video which is only in your head. And then the song finishes and you look at people around you sitting in silence completely unaware of the great music that was jamming in your headphones seconds ago. That is exactly how this book felt. There was so much going on in the book; I would read a bit, completely engrossed, and look around aware of this secret I have in the form of this book which only I am enjoying and nobody else is. <br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I took me a while to understand all the alters of Ashley but I loved the way each one was so different from each other. I loved the character of David Singer even though the court scenes felt repetitive after some time. Every time I made a prediction about something, the author would throw in a twist catching me off guard.<br />Absolutely loved the eerie ending. It deserves an extra star. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Thank you for the recommendation Aditya! :)</span>
  <a data-text-id="726971534003418209" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
